[['CryptoNews.get_recent_articles', {'name': 'CryptoNews.get_recent_articles', 'description': 'This function retrieves recent news articles about specified cryptocurrencies within a given timeframe.', 'required_parameters': [{'name': 'cryptocurrencies', 'type': 'ARRAY', 'description': 'An array of cryptocurrency names to retrieve news for.'}, {'name': 'timeframe', 'type': 'STRING', 'description': 'The timeframe for the news articles, e.g., 1 week, 1 month.'}], 'optional_parameters': [], 'return_data': [{'name': 'articles', 'description': 'A list of up to five news articles for each cryptocurrency.'}]}], ['CryptoPriceAnalysis.analyze_price_impact', {'name': 'CryptoPriceAnalysis.analyze_price_impact', 'description': 'This function analyzes the impact of news articles on the price of specified cryptocurrencies.', 'required_parameters': [{'name': 'articles', 'type': 'ARRAY', 'description': 'An array of article IDs to analyze.'}, {'name': 'cryptocurrencies', 'type': 'ARRAY', 'description': 'An array of cryptocurrency names to analyze the price impact for.'}], 'optional_parameters': [], 'return_data': [{'name': 'impact_analysis', 'description': 'An analysis of how the news articles have affected the price of the cryptocurrencies.'}]}], ['CryptoPriceAnalysis.get_live_prices', {'name': 'CryptoPriceAnalysis.get_live_prices', 'description': 'This function retrieves the live prices of specified cryptocurrencies.', 'required_parameters': [{'name': 'cryptocurrencies', 'type': 'ARRAY', 'description': 'An array of cryptocurrency names to retrieve live prices for.'}], 'optional_parameters': [], 'return_data': [{'name': 'prices', 'description': 'The live prices of the specified cryptocurrencies.'}]}], ['CryptoMarketData.get_trading_volume', {'name': 'CryptoMarketData.get_trading_volume', 'description': 'This function retrieves the trading volume data for specified cryptocurrencies.', 'required_parameters': [{'name': 'cryptocurrencies', 'type': 'ARRAY', 'description': 'An array of cryptocurrency names to retrieve trading volume data for.'}], 'optional_parameters': [], 'return_data': [{'name': 'trading_volume', 'description': 'The trading volume data for the specified cryptocurrencies.'}]}], ['CryptoInvestmentAdvice.provide_investment_tips', {'name': 'CryptoInvestmentAdvice.provide_investment_tips', 'description': 'This function provides investment tips for specified cryptocurrencies.', 'required_parameters': [{'name': 'cryptocurrencies', 'type': 'ARRAY', 'description': 'An array of cryptocurrency names to provide investment tips for.'}], 'optional_parameters': [], 'return_data': [{'name': 'investment_tips', 'description': 'Investment tips for the specified cryptocurrencies.'}]}]]
请生成一个解决用户问题的计划，计划应该是一个行为列表，每个行为的格式如下:

[{
    // 动作的ID
    "id": number;
    // 动作要调用的API名称
    "name": string;
    // 当前API的参数输入(JSON格式)
    "args": "str(Record<string, any>)";
}, ...
]

你可以在计划中想象参数的值，这些指令将按顺序执行。
例如，如果你想调用 `CryptoNews.get_recent_articles` 并传入 `cryptocurrencies` 和 `timeframe`，你可以写下面的计划:

[{
    "id": 0,
    "name": "CryptoNews.get_recent_articles",
    "args": "{'cryptocurrencies': ['bitcoin', 'ethereum'], 'timeframe': '1 week'}",
}, ...
]

这些参数将在执行时被替换为真实的值。请注意，参数应该是一个字符串，而不是一个字典。
请在字典的参数中使用 ''，在其他地方使用 ""，不要打印值为 None 或 null 的参数。

你应该只生成一个 JSON 格式的计划列表。列表应该是完整的计划列表，不要有 `...`。
不要生成任何解释 JSON 的文本。
